results.deck: Konami Computer Entertainment Osaka (KCEO) was founded April 3, 1995 as a subsidiary of Konami Corporation. On March 1, 2003, KCEO's 139 employees were absorbed into a new branch, Konami Studios. This new branch was later absorbed into the parent company in April 2005.
